It may be the power of suggestion but the consensus these last years is the aborption of CBD is likely increased with added oil based supplements taken at the same time. I just want to say that I appreciate your mission to make reliable CBD that's not insanely expensive.

I have long history of anxiety that would result in constant episodes of heart racing and small hand tremors. I was on anti-anxiety medication for a long time (2009-2016), and I was off for a couple of years. The heavy stress that caused me to use them for that whole period was gone, so most of my symptoms were gone - except for the heart-racing and tremors. It reached a point in spring 2019 where it was unmanageable, but I decided to try CBD before going back on medication. It worked wonders, with my heart-racing and tremors only coming out in the highest of stressful times (maybe a few times a year, compared to what used to be daily).

But it was so expensive that after a few months, I thought I'd need to switch back to medication anyway because it was cheaper. Then I did some searching and made the switch to Sunsoil, which was available at my local speciality grocer). And now, with your subscription offerings, I can now afford to take it twice a day for $128 every three months (where before, I'd be paying that much for just one month, which was unsustainable). I also love that you have capsules (before many other brands had capsules), which makes it much easier to get a consistent dose also without dealing with taste and texture.

So thank you for what you do for so many of us, especially when it can help keep us from going back on a medication with so many side effects!
